Overview
  Halcyon Asset Management is a hedge fund based in New York with offices in London, Los Angeles.
   It was founded in 1981 by Alan Slifka.
  They hold $10.0 billion in assets under management as of August 25, 2016.
  Read their Plain English Brochure.

  John Bader is the co-chairman and Chief Investment Officer
