Mr. Desai joined Halcyon in April 2005 and leads and manages the firm's credit investment team. Mr. Desai has spent his career focused on stressed and distressed credit as well as special situations in the U.S, Western Europe, and emerging markets.  His expertise spans multiple sectors, including the financial, technology, energy, industrial, and consumer industries. Prior to joining Halcyon, Mr. Desai began his career at J.P. Morgan Chase, where he was an investment banker working on capital markets transactions. Mr. Desai graduated Summa Cum Laude from The Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania in 2004, where he received a B.S. in Economics with a major in Finance and a minor in History.
 


  


   
 
 















 

